article.headline: Tulsa 66, Arkansas 64
article.story:
FAYETTEVILLE, Ark. (AP) -- Jillian Robbins earned a double-double
with 28 points and 22 rebounds to lead Tulsa to a 66-64 win over
Arkansas on Thursday.

Arkansas (3-3) led by a pair at the half, but Tulsa (3-1) came
back after the break to win by two. Tulsa doubled Arkansas in
offensive rebounds with 32 compared to the Lady Razorbacks' 16.
Overall the Golden Hurricanes had 61 rebounds. Arkansas had 37.

Tulsa had four players in the double-digits with Emily Jaskowiak
and Megan Moody both scoring 11 and Tandem Mays with 10.

Melissa Hobbs led Arkansas with her own double-double of 19
points and 11 rebounds. Kristin Peoples had 15 points off the bench
and starting forward Rochelle Vaughn had 10.

Tulsa scored 22 points off Arkansas' 13 turnovers. But the
Golden Hurricanes committed 22 of their own turnovers, allowing
Arkansas 16 points.

Kristin Moore fouled out for Arkansas.
